File: `package.json` (root), lines 86-93

Current lint-staged config:
```json
"lint-staged": {
  "*.{ts,tsx,json}": [
    "prettier --write",
    "eslint --fix"
  ],
  "*.md": [
    "prettier --write"
  ]
}
```

The issue: `eslint --fix` runs on `*.json` files but the ESLint config (`eslint.config.ts`) only targets `**/*.{ts,tsx}`. ESLint silently skips JSON files (no matching config), but it's still invoked with overhead.

Fix: split into separate patterns:
```json
"lint-staged": {
  "*.{ts,tsx}": [
    "prettier --write",
    "eslint --fix"
  ],
  "*.json": [
    "prettier --write"
  ],
  "*.md": [
    "prettier --write"
  ]
}
```

This is a one-line structural change in package.json. Ensure the JSON is valid after editing.
